{
  "texts": [
    "When following a procedural plan through a dialogue, there are many dependencies and unexpected events that may occur during its execution.",
    "Tutoring systems try to cover all possible events and define a complex mesh of dependencies and actions (Kumar and Rosé, 2011).",
    "In control theory, the revision and generation of a new procedural plan are now being tackled with LLMs and neuralsymbolic methods (Lu et al., 2022).",
    "Generating data for instruction datasets using general-purpose LLMs is an active research topic.",
    "Task2Dial (Strathearn and Gkatzia, 2022) is especially relevant, as it contains realistic dialogues centered around recipes, and makes use of commonsense knowledge throughout."
  ]
}